Let's think step by step. Using the distributive property, we expand the first term:
\begin{align*}
x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2) & = xx(1+x)+2xx-3(x^2-x+2)\\
& = x^2(1+x)+2xx-3x^2+3x-6\\
& = x^2+3x^2-x-6\\
& = (4-1)x^2-(1-6)x-6\\
& = \boxed{3x^2-5x-6}
\end{align*}
